<paragraph id="8BA336ADFFBB2468FF1710CA1EA5D0D4" blockId="6.[151,724,1159,1185]" box="[151,724,1159,1185]" pageId="6" pageNumber="46">
<heading id="D0EB81C1FFBB2468FF1710CA1EA5D0D4" bold="true" box="[151,724,1159,1185]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="6" pageNumber="46" reason="1">
<emphasis id="B968EABFFFBB2468FF1710CA1EA5D0D4" bold="true" box="[151,724,1159,1185]" pageId="6" pageNumber="46">
Key to the 
<collectingCountry id="F30B763DFFBB2468FE9F10CA1DCBD0D4" box="[287,442,1159,1185]" name="Madagascar" pageId="6" pageNumber="46">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C1C4D2EFFBB2468FDBE10CA1EA5D0D4" box="[574,724,1159,1185]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Betasyrphus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B968EABFFFBB2468FDBE10CA1EA5D0D4" bold="true" box="[574,724,1159,1185]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="46">Betasyrphus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA336ADFFBB2468FF17109D1D0AD10A" blockId="6.[151,1436,1232,1407]" pageId="6" pageNumber="46">
Note that the males of 
<taxonomicName id="4C1C4D2EFFBB2468FE25109D1E2DD09C" box="[421,604,1232,1257]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Betasyrphus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="stuckenbergi">
<emphasis id="B968EABFFFBB2468FE25109D1E2DD09C" box="[421,604,1232,1257]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="46">B. stuckenbergi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are not yet known and therefore are not included in the key. However the very long antennae will presumably also be present in the male sex and key out correctly. Both species have a completely yellow face, while a large proportion of the other Afrotropical species have a dark knob or median vitta on the face. For more distinctive characters and separation of the Oriental and Palaearctic 
<taxonomicName id="4C1C4D2EFFBB2468FA02110D1C86D10B" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Syrphus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="serarius">
<emphasis id="B968EABFFFBB2468FA02110D1C86D10B" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="46">B. serarius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
see 
<tableCitation id="C69E0316FFBB2468FEAB11281D0AD10A" box="[299,379,1381,1407]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="7.[151,239,588,612]" captionTargetBox="[151,1427,639,1948]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="TABLE 1. Diagnostic characters of Betasyrphus keiseri sp. n., B. serarius (Wiedemann) and B. stuckenbergi (Keiser)" httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/DF636625FFBA2469FF171601190ED611" pageId="6" pageNumber="46" tableUuid="DF636625FFBA2469FF171601190ED611">
Tab. 
<number id="3DD4248AFFBB2468FEE511281D04D10A" box="[357,373,1381,1407]" pageId="6" pageNumber="46" value="1.0">1</number>
.
</tableCitation>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3066526FFBB2468FF1711FF19EDD2B9" pageId="6" pageNumber="46" type="key">
<keyStep id="30E82E08FFBB2468FF1711FF19EDD2B9" pageId="6" pageNumber="46">
<paragraph id="8BA336ADFFBB2468FF1711FF19EAD23C" blockId="6.[151,1436,1456,1740]" pageId="6" pageNumber="46">
<keyLead id="30ED9598FFBB2468FF1711FF19EAD23C" pageId="6" pageNumber="46">
<number id="3DD4248AFFBB2468FF1711FF1CD5D1BC" box="[151,164,1458,1481]" pageId="6" pageNumber="46" value="1.0">1</number>
Antennae with basoflagellomere (
<number id="3DD4248AFFBB2468FDB711FF1E35D1BC" box="[567,580,1458,1481]" pageId="6" pageNumber="46" value="3.0">3</number>
rd joint) very elongated, three times longer than wide (measurements on female 
<typeStatus id="54A7880FFFBB2468FF47119F1D55D19C" box="[199,292,1490,1513]" pageId="6" pageNumber="46">holotype</typeStatus>
and 
<typeStatus id="54A7880FFFBB2468FED8119F1DC6D19C" box="[344,439,1490,1513]" pageId="6" pageNumber="46">paratype</typeStatus>
; only other Afrotropical species with very long antennae is 
<taxonomicName id="4C1C4D2EFFBB2468FBB4119F191ED19C" authority="Bezzi, 1915" authorityName="Bezzi" authorityYear="1915" box="[1076,1391,1490,1513]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Betasyrphus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="inflaticornis">
<emphasis id="B968EABFFFBB2468FBB4119F18A5D19C" box="[1076,1236,1490,1513]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="46">B. inflaticornis</emphasis>
(Bezzi, 
<number id="3DD4248AFFBB2468FAAE119F1916D19C" box="[1326,1383,1490,1513]" pageId="6" pageNumber="46" value="1915.0">1915</number>
)
</taxonomicName>
, not known from 
<collectingCountry id="F30B763DFFBB2468FED511BF1DA7D27C" box="[341,470,1522,1545]" name="Madagascar" pageId="6" pageNumber="46">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
and differentiated by a dark facial knob). Wing hyaline without dark maculae. Anterior part of wing yellowish. Abdomen appearing almost black with only vague maculae on tergite 
<number id="3DD4248AFFBB2468FB2F125F18CFD25C" box="[1199,1214,1554,1577]" pageId="6" pageNumber="46" value="3.0">3</number>
, on tergite 
<number id="3DD4248AFFBB2468FAB5125F1933D25C" box="[1333,1346,1554,1577]" pageId="6" pageNumber="46" value="2.0">2</number>
missing (description from females only)........................................................................................ 
<taxonomicName id="4C1C4D2EFFBB2468FBEF127F19EAD23C" authority="Keiser 1971" authorityName="Keiser" authorityYear="1971" box="[1135,1435,1586,1609]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Betasyrphus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="stuckenbergi">
<emphasis id="B968EABFFFBB2468FBEF127F1962D23C" box="[1135,1299,1586,1609]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="46">B. stuckenbergi</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF8D4B5CFFBB2468FA9A127F19EAD23C" author="Keiser" box="[1306,1435,1586,1609]" pageId="6" pageNumber="49" refString="Keiser, F. (1971) Syrphidae von Madagaskar (Dipt.). Verhandlungen der Naturforschenden Gesellschaft in Basel 81, 223 - 318 [date on the cover 1970, available printed 1971]." type="journal article" year="1971">
Keiser 
<number id="3DD4248AFFBB2468FAE6127F19EAD23C" box="[1382,1435,1586,1609]" pageId="6" pageNumber="46" value="1971.0">1971</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA336ADFFBB2468FF17121819EDD2B9" blockId="6.[151,1436,1456,1740]" pageId="6" pageNumber="46">
<keyLead id="30ED9598FFBB2468FF17121819EDD2B9" pageId="6" pageNumber="46">
- Antennae with basoflagellomere (
<number id="3DD4248AFFBB2468FDB612181E32D219" box="[566,579,1621,1644]" pageId="6" pageNumber="46" value="3.0">3</number>
rd joint) one and a half to two times as long as wide. Wing hyaline usually with distinct brownish macula (clearly developed in most males, weaker and sometimes missing in the females and part of the males), see 
<figureCitation id="13272A28FFBB2468FE0812D81DA7D2D9" box="[392,470,1685,1708]" captionStart="FIGURES 12, 13" captionStartId="4.[151,269,1942,1966]" captionText="FIGURES 12, 13. Wing of Betysyrphus keiseri sp. n., Photo of wing with diffuse darkened patch (Fig. 12) and schematic drawing of mictotrichia coverage and pile on lower calypter (Fig. 13)." pageId="6" pageNumber="46">
Fig. 
<number id="3DD4248AFFBB2468FE3912D81DA7D2D9" box="[441,470,1685,1708]" pageId="6" pageNumber="46" value="12.0">12</number>
</figureCitation>
. Fasciae on tergites 
<number id="3DD4248AFFBB2468FD2E12D81ECDD2D9" box="[686,700,1685,1708]" pageId="6" pageNumber="46" value="2.0">2</number>
+ 
<number id="3DD4248AFFBB2468FD4B12D81EA6D2D9" box="[715,727,1685,1708]" pageId="6" pageNumber="46" value="3.0">3</number>
distinct and widely separated from their anterior margin............... 
<emphasis id="B968EABFFFBB2468FF4E12F81931D2B9" box="[206,1344,1717,1740]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="46">
........................................................................................................................................................... 
<taxonomicName id="4C1C4D2EFFBB2468FB5B12F81931D2B9" box="[1243,1344,1717,1740]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Betasyrphus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="keiseri" status="sp. nov.">B. keiseri</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A25B57C4FFBB2468FAC712F919EDD2B9" box="[1351,1436,1716,1740]" pageId="6" pageNumber="46" rank="species">
